    "created_at": "2016-09-21T10:15:53Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-09-21T10:15:53Z",
    "body": "When this PR was first submitted I was all :+1: on this, but having spent some time recently fighting a table in a markdown document I have changed my opinion to :-1::-1::-1:. Basically, your standard markdown table syntax doesn't allow line breaks within a cell, so you end up with these crazy long lines with embedded `<br>` tags (to force line breaks), so readability plummets. Then you realize you can embed an HTML `<table>` in the document so you can have (a somewhat, but not really) more readable document, only to discover that GitHub will throw your inline styles into the gutter and render your table however it pleases. Finally, you end up using deprecated HTML 4 attributes to force proper alignment of cell content. Victory at last! But was it worth it? Not really.\n"
  },
