    "created_at": "2016-09-21T22:50:20Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-09-21T22:50:20Z",
    "body": "> markdown table syntax doesn't allow line breaks within a cell, so you end up with these crazy long lines\n\nI tend to agree with this sentiment. We have to consider that developers are consuming this documentation in a variety of ways. Some of them include:\n- [https://github.com/electron/electron/docs](github.com/electron/electron/docs)\n- [http://electron.atom.io/docs](electron.atom.io/docs)\n- Right inside the `$EDITOR`\n\n#7120 shipped recently, and the next [release](https://github.com/electron/electron/releases) of Electron (1.4.1) will include an `electron-api.json` file that describes all the APIs. I think a better way to reach tabular utopia would be to use this new structured data to render dynamic templates on electron.atom.io (or elsewhere). This will allow us a lot more flexibility in how we render and style the docs.\n\nNot seeing a lot of strong reactions either way from people here, so I'm going to close this out in favor of that approach.\n"
